01:55:45.720 --> 01:55:49.580
in terms of explosive energy. Yeah, so
all of those questions together. So

01:55:49.680 --> 01:55:51.280
how hard is it to produce antimatter?

01:55:52.020 --> 01:55:55.790
- It's freaking hard. Okay.
All right. So here's the

01:55:55.840 --> 01:55:59.700
deal. So at the time until two
thousand and eleven, Fermilab

01:55:59.780 --> 01:56:03.420
was the most powerful antiproton

01:56:03.500 --> 01:56:07.380
production facility on the planet.
Every two point three seconds,

01:56:08.200 --> 01:56:12.360
we would smash ten to the
thirteen protons into a target,

01:56:13.220 --> 01:56:17.140
and we would get out ten
to the eighth antiprotons.

01:56:17.220 --> 01:56:21.080
So basically, in order to
get a single antiproton, we

01:56:21.160 --> 01:56:25.920
needed to smash a hundred
thousand protons into material.

01:56:26.960 --> 01:56:30.180
So every two point three
seconds, we would get of order

01:56:30.700 --> 01:56:34.120
ten to the eighth antiprotons.
And what we would

01:56:34.160 --> 01:56:38.140
do is we would collect them over
the course of twelve hours or

01:56:38.200 --> 01:56:42.160
so, and we would get, in the end,
we would have to collect them and

01:56:42.300 --> 01:56:46.100
cool them down and so forth, of
order ten to the twelfth antiprotons

01:56:46.180 --> 01:56:50.140
every twelve to twenty-four
hours. So ten to the

01:56:50.200 --> 01:56:54.020
twelfth sounds like a lot. It
really does. That is a trillion.

01:56:54.700 --> 01:56:58.600
But you need to remember that
a gram of antimatter is ten to

01:56:58.640 --> 01:57:02.600
the twenty-three antiprotons.
So that means over

01:57:02.640 --> 01:57:09.200
the course of a day, we were able to
create something like one hundred

01:57:09.360 --> 01:57:15.220
billionth of a gram. And so
if we did that for a year,

01:57:16.140 --> 01:57:19.940
then that would be about a nanogram. So
about a nanogram a year, give or take.

01:57:20.360 --> 01:57:24.260
That's a reasonable estimate. So a

01:57:24.440 --> 01:57:28.220
nanogram, one billionth of a
gram, so that means at that

01:57:28.320 --> 01:57:32.140
rate, with that facility, it would
take a billion years running

01:57:32.200 --> 01:57:35.900
